# **Topological–Geometrical Descriptor (TGD) for 2D Carbon Systems**

This repository provides an implementation of the **Topological–Geometrical Descriptor (TGD)**, a **physically interpretable**, **topology-aware**, and **geometry-informed** descriptor specifically designed for **two-dimensional sp/sp² carbon systems**.

The **TGD** maps atomistic structures into a compact and meaningful set of **topological** and **geometrical observables** extracted from the **planar bonding graph** and its associated **ring statistics**. In contrast to purely abstract numerical encodings, the descriptor is explicitly constructed to preserve direct correspondence with the **bonding topology**, **ring organization**, **defect physics**, and **geometric heterogeneity** of the lattice.

It was developed to characterize a broad class of carbon-based materials, including **graphene**, **defect-rich carbon allotropes**, and **porous 2D carbon networks**, while maintaining a strong emphasis on **interpretability**, **physical consistency**, and **structural insight**.

## **Main contents of this repository**

The repository includes:

- **`descriptor_TGD.py`**: main code for generating the **TGD** directly from crystal structures in **`.cif`** format
- **`structure/`**: example structural database containing representative **2D carbon systems**
- **`interpretability.py`**: post-processing and interpretability analysis code for reading the generated descriptors and producing figures for structural analysis

## **Repository structure**

```bash
.
├── descriptor_TGD.py
├── interpretability.py
├── structure/
│   ├── graphene.cif
